SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 110
BY SENATOR MYERS
COMMENDATIONS. Commends the students and faculty of the Lafayette Parish School
System for their placement of first-overall in the Louisiana Governor's Games' 31st Annual
Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate the students and faculty of the Lafayette Parish School
3 System for their placement of first-overall in the Louisiana Governor's Games' thirty-
4 first Annual Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet.
5 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Governor's Games are the state's premier amateur
6 sporting event; and
7 WHEREAS, the Lafayette Parish School System finished first-overall in the thirty-
8 first Annual Elementary State Championship Fitness Meet; and
9 WHEREAS, Lafayette Parish secured first place with a total of 2,479 points ahead
10 of second-place St. Tammany Parish with 2,459 points, and third-place Rapides Parish with
11 2,428 points; and
12 WHEREAS, the elementary fitness meet competition involves seven fitness-related
13 events, including the 50-yard dash, the shuttle run, pull-ups, the standing long-jump, curl-ups
14 or sit-ups, the 600-yard run, and the V-sit and reach; and
15 WHEREAS, the top two boys and girls from each parish travel to Alexandria
16 annually to compete for the fitness title; and
17 WHEREAS, Lafayette Parish's top performer, Tianna Franks, led the way with 648
18 individual points; and
